{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nCLAUDE.md's 'Gate protocols (MANDATORY)' section (CLAUDE.md:112-121) instructs agents that even on a PASS they 'must remediate all valid advisory findings before continuing'. Field data: ~13 advisories/round, 95% of remediation edits mint new findings, and the mandated loop drove the 4+-round tail that consumed 60% of gate compute. With the convergence floors now default-ON (change 562) the operator wants to LOOSEN this guidance — NOT replace it with guidance to ignore advisories — and observe whether agents implement advisories properly on their own judgment.\n\n## What\n- Edit CLAUDE.md's plan-review protocol paragraph (~lines 118-120): remove the MUST-remediate-all-valid-advisories mandate. Replace with neutral judgment framing, e.g.: review the advisory findings and coaching notes; apply the ones that genuinely improve the plan; a blocking verdict must still be remediated and re-reviewed. Do NOT add language discouraging advisory uptake.\n- Sweep for echoes of the mandate across ALL agent-facing docs — `CLAUDE.md`, `docs/`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, AND `examples/` (the committed skill copies). The known echo is `examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md:136` ('remediate every valid finding'): soften it to the same judgment-based framing (apply the advisories that genuinely improve the plan) while KEEPING its BLOCK-must-remediate / re-run-until-pass instruction intact. The completion-verifier protocol paragraph stays UNCHANGED (close FAILs remain mandatory-remediate). The 'Sign on every round' and BLOCK-must-remediate guidance stays verbatim.\n- The observation plan (compare advisory-uptake rate and rounds-to-pass before/after via REVIEW_RESULT sidecars — `norm_id` survival across rounds = an advisory was addressed) is recorded on the parent epic's measurement-framework AC (epic 9d50 AC2), not duplicated here.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The mandate is GONE and the replacement framing is judgment-based. Two-sided proof: (negative) `grep -niE \"remediate all valid advisory|must remediate all valid\" CLAUDE.md` returns NOTHING; (positive) `grep -n \"apply the ones that genuinely improve the plan\" CLAUDE.md` returns the new sentence AND `grep -n \"not a mandate to remediate every advisory\" CLAUDE.md` returns the clause that explicitly frames uptake as a judgment call (not discouragement).\n- [ ] BLOCK-remediation and sign-every-round guidance are unchanged (present-phrase proof): `grep -n \"you must \\*\\*remediate the failure\" CLAUDE.md` still shows the blocking-verdict-must-be-remediated clause, and `grep -n \"Sign on every round\" CLAUDE.md` still returns the verbatim paragraph.\n- [ ] No other agent-facing doc still states the mandatory-advisory-remediation rule, and the one known echo is softened to judgment framing. Two-sided proof over `CLAUDE.md docs/ CONTRIBUTING.md examples/`: (negative) `grep -rniE \"remediate every valid finding|remediate all valid advisor\" <those paths>` returns NOTHING; (positive) `grep -n \"apply the advisory findings that genuinely improve the plan\" examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md` returns the softened line, which still retains its \"remediate any blocking finding and re-run until it passes\" instruction.\n- [ ] make lint passes on the change.\n- [ ] make test passes on the change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783887480429279001,"uuid":"e322506c-dce8-4d23-a303-68fe259d4416"}